Steps 2–10 — Build the table
(Same flow as L1-A02; copy-paste safe; pause anywhere.)
Step 2 — Properties tab
In make.powerapps.com → EMS solution → + New → Table → Table → Properties tab:
Display name:
BP-to-BU Mapping
Description:
Maps Parent Business Process identifiers from Archer to normalized Business Units. Flow 1 writes new entries when it encounters unmapped BPs; admins assign Target BU to resolve them.
Plural name: auto-fills to BP-to-BU Mappings — leave it.
Expand Advanced options:

Schema name: verify BPtoBUMapping (full logical: pei_BPtoBUMapping)
Type: Standard
Record ownership: User or team
Enable for: ☑ Auditing, ☑ Activities, ☑ Notes, ☑ Connections

⚠️ Don't Save yet — set Primary column on next tab.
Step 3 — Primary column tab
Display name:
Parent Business Process Identifier
Description:
The verbatim Parent Business Process identifier as it appears in Archer (e.g., "BP-001", "PROC-FIN"). Must be unique. Note: Power Platform stores the logical name as pei_Name regardless of display name; flow code must reference pei_Name, not pei_parentbusinessprocessidentifier.
Data type: Single line of text
Expand Advanced options:

Schema name: auto-fills to Name
Maximum character count: 200
Required: Business required

Step 4 — Save the table
Click Save. Wait ~15-30 sec.
Step 5 — Add column: Target BU (lookup)
Columns area → + New column:

Display name: Target BU
Description: The Business Unit this Parent BP maps to. Null when status is Unresolved.
Data type: Lookup
Related table: Business Unit — be careful to pick the one with pei_businessunit logical name (your custom one), NOT the Microsoft system businessunit. Type pei_ in the search box to filter to custom tables.
Required: Optional
Advanced → Schema name: targetbu
Click Save.

Step 6 — Add column: Status (choice)
+ New column:

Display name: Status
Description: Whether this Parent BP has been mapped to a BU, deliberately ignored, or is still unresolved.
Data type: Choice
Sync this choice with: New choice (NOT existing — we're using a local copy, not the global option set)
Choice items:

Label: Unresolved, Value: 890920000
Label: Mapped, Value: 890920001
Label: Ignored, Value: 890920002


Default choice: Unresolved
Required: Business required
Advanced → Schema name: edit to mappingstatus (so logical becomes pei_mappingstatus, not pei_status)
Click Save.

Step 7 — Add column: Notes
+ New column:

Display name: Notes
Description: Admin notes about this BP mapping (e.g., why ignored, ambiguity flags, who to consult).
Data type: Multiple lines of text
Format: Text (plain — NOT Rich text)
Maximum character count: 2000
Required: Optional
Click Save.

Step 8 — Add column: First Seen
+ New column:

Display name: First Seen
Description: Timestamp when Flow 1 first encountered this Parent BP identifier in an Archer export.
Data type: Date and Time
Format: Date and time
Required: Optional
Advanced → Schema name: firstseen
Click Save.

Step 9 — Add column: Affected Records
+ New column:

Display name: Affected Records
Description: Count of Control Procedure records currently associated with this Parent BP. Updated by Flow 1 each cycle.
Data type: Whole Number
Minimum value: 0
Required: Optional
Advanced → Schema name: affectedrecords
Click Save.

Step 10 — Add Alternate Key
Keys area → + New key:

Display name: BP Identifier Unique
Columns: select Parent Business Process Identifier
Click Save (background job ~30-60 sec; key shows "Active" when done).
